  <section class="faq-section"><div class="container">
    <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">FAQs</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p>Common questions about virtual credit cards</p></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Can I use a virtual credit card at physical stores?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, by adding your virtual card to a mobile wallet like Google Pay, Apple Pay, or Samsung Pay. Once added, you can tap-to-pay at any NFC-enabled POS terminal. You can also link your virtual card to UPI (available for RuPay and select Visa/Mastercard cards) and scan QR codes at any UPI-accepting merchant. However, you cannot swipe or insert a virtual card into a traditional card reader — for that, you'll need the physical version. Most banks offer the physical card on request alongside the virtual card.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Are virtual credit cards safe for online shopping?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Virtual credit cards are actually safer than physical cards for online shopping. Key security advantages: (1) You can generate unique card numbers per merchant, so a data breach at one store doesn't expose your main card, (2) Instant freeze/unfreeze controls let you disable the card in seconds if you suspect fraud, (3) Real-time transaction alerts notify you of every charge, (4) Spending limits can be set per virtual card, (5) No physical card to lose or get skimmed. The card details are stored in encrypted format within the banking app, protected by biometric authentication.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">How quickly can I get a virtual credit card?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">For pre-approved customers (existing bank account holders), virtual credit cards can be issued in under 60 seconds after accepting the offer in the banking app. For new applicants, the process takes 2-10 minutes including e-KYC (Aadhaar OTP or video verification). Digital-first issuers like OneCard and Fi typically complete the entire process in under 5 minutes. Traditional banks like HDFC and ICICI issue the virtual card instantly after loan approval, which may take a few hours to 1-2 days for verification if not pre-approved.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Can I link a virtual credit card to UPI?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, credit cards on UPI is now widely supported in India. RuPay credit cards can be linked to all major UPI apps (Google Pay, PhonePe, Paytm, BHIM). Select Visa and Mastercard credit cards can also be linked to UPI through specific banking apps. Once linked, you can scan any UPI QR code and pay using your credit card — the amount gets charged to your card's credit limit rather than your bank account. This effectively lets you earn credit card rewards on UPI payments, which was previously impossible.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Do virtual cards earn the same rewards as physical cards?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, virtual cards and physical cards share the same card account, so all rewards, cashback, and benefits apply equally regardless of which form you use. Transactions made with the virtual card number earn the same reward points as those made with the physical card. The billing, interest rates, credit limit, and payment due dates are also identical — the virtual card is simply a digital representation of the same credit card account. There is no separate reward structure for virtual versus physical usage.</div></div></div>
    </div>
